metadata.name: The Rainbow After the Storm
metadata.description:
Tectonic plates may shift and shake  
Dinosaurs may roam and quake  
But through it all, the sky remains  
A canvas painted in vibrant strains

Magic fills the air, a guiding light  
Adventure waits to take flight  
Love, the greatest force of all  
Will catch us when we stumble and fall

For every storm that rages on  
A rainbow will appear, a beacon strong  
And as the sunlight warms our hearts  
We'll find the strength to make a new start

So hold on tight, dear friend of mine  
Everything will be okay in time  
For no matter what the future holds  
We'll brave the journey, brave and bold
